# <type>(<scope>): <subject>        | 50 chars max title, no period --|
#                                                                          |
# Detailed explanation of the change. Wrap text at 72 characters.         |
# Include motivation for the change and contrast with previous behavior.  |
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── |
# Example:                                                                |
# feat(auth): implement JWT-based authentication                          |
#                                                                        |
# Add secure authentication system with role-based access control:       |
# - Create login/signup endpoints with rate limiting                     |
# - Add token validation middleware                                      |
# - Implement password hashing with bcrypt                              |
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── |
#                                                                        |
# Type Options:                                                          |
#   feat     - A new feature                                            |
#   fix      - A bug fix                                                |
#   docs     - Documentation only changes                               |
#   style    - Changes not affecting code (formatting, etc)             |
#   refactor - Code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds feature    |
#   perf     - Code change that improves performance                    |
#   test     - Adding missing tests or correcting existing tests        |
#   chore    - Changes to build process or auxiliary tools              |
#   ci       - Changes to CI configuration files and scripts            |
#                                                                        |
# Scope Options:                                                         |
#   auth     - Authentication related                                    |
#   api      - API related changes                                      |
#   ui       - User interface components                                |
#   db       - Database related                                         |
#   workflow - Development workflow                                      |
#   deps     - Dependencies                                             |
#   config   - Configuration changes                                    |
#                                                                        |
# Breaking Changes:                                                      |
# Start with "BREAKING CHANGE:" followed by description and migration    |
# steps if applicable.                                                   |
#                                                                        |
# Example:                                                               |
# BREAKING CHANGE: Remove support for Node 14                            |
# Node 16 or higher is now required for all build processes.            |
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── |
#                                                                        |
# Rules:                                                                 |
# 1. Subject line:                                                       |
#    - Use imperative mood ("add" not "added")                          |
#    - No period at end                                                 |
#    - 50 characters max                                                |
#    - Capitalize first letter                                          |
#                                                                        |
# 2. Body:                                                              |
#    - Separate from subject with blank line                            |
#    - Wrap at 72 characters                                            |
#    - Use bullet points for multiple items                             |
#    - Explain what and why vs. how                                     |
#                                                                        |
# 3. Breaking Changes:                                                   |
#    - Start with "BREAKING CHANGE:"                                     |
#    - Include migration instructions                                    |
#    - Separate from body with blank line                               |
#                                                                        |
# 4. References:                                                         |
#    - Reference issues at bottom: "Closes #123, #456"                  |
#    - Reference PRs: "See PR #789"                                     |
#                                                                        |
# Multi-line Commit Command:                                            |
# git commit -m "feat(auth): implement JWT authentication" \             |
#   -m "" \                                                             |
#   -m "Add secure authentication system with role-based access:" \     |
#   -m "- Create login/signup endpoints" \                              |
#   -m "- Add token validation" \                                       |
#   -m "" \                                                             |
#   -m "BREAKING CHANGE: Require Authorization header" \                |
#   -m "" \                                                             |
#   -m "Closes #123"                                                    |
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── |
